        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 5:20PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 519 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Haswell to near
Arlington to near Crowley. Movement was north at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ordway, Manzanola, Sugar City, Crowley, Haswell, Blue Lake, and
Arlington.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
